children.text: The rear of the brickwork has not been properly packed with mortar to prevent the lintel twisting.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 4773 Masonry for Small Buildings, clause 8.2.2 Detailing of steel lintels states that
‘The gap between the vertical leg of a steel angle lintel and the masonry shall be packed with mortar as shown in Figure 8.3’
‘The mortar pack is required to prevent twisting of the lintel’ .
This area of brickwork will need to be rectified so that the lintel cannot twist, and adequately support the brickwork over it as required by this Australian Standard.
